{"parse":{"title":"tree","pageid":4120,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|tree-|Tree|TREE|tréë}}\n==English==\n{{picdic\n|image=Birnbaum am Lerchenberg retouched.jpg\n|text=tree (1)\n|detail1=\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Brunfelsia pauciflora shrub.jpg|link=plant}}\n|detail3=<!-- Meronyms -->\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Roots by cesarpb.jpg|link=root}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Magnolia acuminata trunk.JPG|link=trunk}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Ceiba sp branches.jpg|link=branch}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Autumn Red Oak Leaf.jpg|link=leaf}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Picea koyamae shoot.JPG|link=needle}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Fruit_Stall_in_Barcelona_Market.jpg|link=fruit}}\n}}\n[[Image:Grid-tree.svg|thumb|A tree structure]]\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|en|id=plant|:inh|enm:tre<id:tree>|tree=1}}\n{{PIE word|en|dóru}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|trau}}, {{m|enm|tre}}, {{m|enm|tree}}, {{m|enm|treo}}, {{m|enm|treou}}, {{m|enm|trew}}, {{m|enm|trewe}}, {{m|enm|troe}}, {{m|enm|trouȝh}}, {{m|enm|trouȝgh}}, {{m|enm|trow}}, {{m|enm|trowe}}, from {{inh|en|ang|trēo}}, {{m|ang|trēow}}, {{m|ang|trēu}}, {{m|ang|trīo}}, {{m|ang|trīow}}, {{m|ang|trȳw|t=tree; wood; forest; beam, cudgel, log; cross}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*treu}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*trewą|t=tree}}, from pre-Germanic {{m|ine-pro|*dréwom}}, thematic e-grade derivative of {{inh|en|ine-pro|*dóru|t=tree}}. Related to {{m|en|tar}}, {{m|en|true}}.\n{{col-top|2|cog}}\nCognate with {{cog|nl|teer|t=tree}}, {{cog|da,fo,gmq-scy|træ|t=tree; timber, wood}}, {{cog|ovd|trai|t=tree; timber, wood}}, {{cog|is|tré|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|nb,nn|tre|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|sv|trä|t=wood; tree}}, {{m|sv|träd|t=tree}}, {{cog|got|𐍄𐍂𐌹𐌿|t=piece of wood}}; also {{cog|br|derv|t=oak}}, {{cog|kw|dar|t=oak}}, {{cog|ga|dair|t=oak}}, {{cog|gv|darragh|t=oak; oaken}}, {{cog|gd|darach|t=oak}}, {{cog|cy|dâr|t=oak}}, {{cog|grc|δόρυ|t=tree; wood; spear}} (whence {{cog|el|δόρυ|t=pike, spear}}), {{cog|sq|dru|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|lv|darva|t=tar}}, {{cog|lt|derva|t=tar; resin}}, {{cog|be|дзе́рава|t=tree}}, {{m|be|дрэ́ва|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|cs|drvo}}, {{m|cs|dřevo|t=wood}}, {{cog|pl|drzewo|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|ru|де́рево}}, {{m|ru|дре́во|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|sh|др̏во}}, {{m|sh|drȇvo}}, {{m|sh|drijȇvo}}, {{m|sh|drȋvo}}, {{m|sh|dȑvo|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|sk,sl|drevo|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|uk|де́рево|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|hy|տարր|t=element; component}}, {{cog|ae|𐬛𐬁𐬎𐬭𐬎|t=wood}}, {{cog|ckb,fa|دار|tr=dâr|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|kmr|dar|t=tree}}, {{cog|zza|dare|t=tree}}, {{cog|hit|𒋫𒊒|tr=taru}}, {{m|hit|𒋫𒀀𒊒|tr=táru|t=tree; wood}}, {{cog|xlu|𒋫𒀀𒊒|tr=tāru|t=wood}}, {{cog|xto,txb|or|t=wood}}, {{cog|sa|दारु|t=timber, wood}}.\n{{col-bottom}}\nReplaced alternative {{ncog|enm|beem}}, from {{ncog|ang|bēam}} (see {{m|en|beam}}) and eclipsed non-native {{ncog|enm|arbre}}, borrowed from {{ncog|fro|arbre}}. \n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alt|en|tre||obsolete}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{enPR|trē}}, {{IPA|en|/tɹiː/|[t̠ʰɹʷiː]|[t͡ʃʰɹʷiː]|[t̠͡ɹ̠̊˔ʷiː]}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Back ache-tree.wav|a=RP}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-tree.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Naomi Persephone Amethyst (NaomiAmethyst)-tree.wav|a=GA}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-tree.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{homophones|en|three|aa=th-stopping}}\n* {{rhymes|en|iː|s=1}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|s|treen<l:obsolete>}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q10884}} A [[perennial]] [[woody]] [[plant]] taller and larger than a [[shrub]] with a wooden trunk and, at some distance from the ground, having leaves and branches.\n#: {{hyper|en|plant<id:Q756>|<|organism<id:Q7239>}}\n#: {{cot|en|shrub#Noun|bush#Noun|grass#Noun<qq:fellow terrestrial plants>}}\n#: {{ux|en|Hyperion is the tallest living '''tree''' in the world.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Birds have a nest in a '''tree''' in the garden.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|date=April 5 1992|chapter=[[w:List of Jeeves and Wooster episodes|The Full House]]|title=w:Jeeves and Wooster|section=Series 3, Episode 2\n|passage=''B. Wooster:'' Of all the places on this great planet of ours, West Neck, Long Island, has chosen to be the most unexciting. The last time anything ''remotely'' interesting happened here was in 1842, when a '''tree''' fell over. They still talk about it in the village.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2019|month=October|author=Ian Walmsley|title=Cleaning up|journal=Modern Railways|page=42|text=When we see a train trapped behind (or embedded in) a fallen '''tree''' our first thought should be 'what was it doing there anyway?' {{...}}'''Trees''' are also responsible for numerous minor delays in autumn <small>[due to leaves falling on the track]</small>, which rolling stock engineers are supposed to cope with as usual.}}\n# Any other [[plant]] (such as a large shrub or herb) that is [[reminiscent]] of the above in form and size.\n#: {{ux|en|The banana '''tree''' is a tall perennial herb: its trunk is not woody.}}\n# An object made from a tree trunk and having multiple [[hook]]s or storage [[platform|platforms]].\n#: {{ux|en|He had the choice of buying a scratching post or a cat '''tree'''.}}\n# A device used to hold or stretch a shoe open.\n#: {{ux|en|He put a shoe '''tree''' in each of his shoes.}} <!-- Move to [[shoe tree]]? -->\n# The structural [[frame]] of a [[saddle]].\n# {{lb|en|graph theory}} A connected [[graph]] with no cycles or, if the graph is finite, equivalently a connected graph with ''n'' vertices and ''n''−1 edges.\n# {{lb|en|computing theory}} A [[recursive]] [[data structure]] in which each [[node]] has zero or more nodes as children, but does not share children with other nodes.\n# {{lb|en|graphical user interface}} A [[display]] or listing of [[entry|entries]] or [[element]]s such that there are [[primary]] and [[secondary]] entries shown, usually linked by drawn lines or by indenting to the right.\n#: {{ux|en|We’ll show it as a '''tree''' list.}}\n# Any [[structure]] or [[construct]] having [[branch]]es representing [[divergence]] or possible [[choice]]s.\n#: {{ux|en|[[family '''tree''']]; [[skill '''tree''']]}}\n# {{senseid|en|saddle}} The [[structure]] or [[wooden]] [[frame]] used in the construction of a [[saddle]] used in horse riding.\n# {{lb|en|often in the plural|slang}} [[marijuana|Marijuana]].\n#* {{quote-song|en|lyricist=w:Eminem; w:Nate Dogg|composer=|title=w:Shake That|url=|album=Curtain Call: The Hits|artist=|year=2005|passage=I like good pussy and I like good '''trees''' / Smoke so much weed you wouldn't believe}}\n#* {{RQ:Big Shaq Man's Not Hot|passage=Everyday man's on the block / Smoke '''trees''' (ah)}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|title=Ace|feat=Smino & Saba|album=Room 25|artist={{w|Noname (rapper)|Noname}}| url=https://nonameraps.bandcamp.com/album/room-25| year=2018| passage=Whiskey with the team, got it bubblin' / I got '''trees''' in my luggage, I got tings out in London / Hope UK, what you say? Fuck is you sayin'?}}\n# {{lb|en|archaic|outside|Christianity}} A [[cross]] or [[gallows]].\n#: {{ux|en|[[Tyburn tree|Tyburn '''tree''']]}}\n#* {{RQ:King James Version|Acts|5|30|passage=The God of our fathers raised up Jesus, whom ye slew and hanged on a '''tree'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Tempest|III|ii|page=12|passage=[[w:Stephano (The Tempest)|''Ste[phano].'']] ''Trinculo'', keepe a good tongue in your head: If you proue a mutineere, the next '''Tree''':{{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1707|author={{w|Isaac Watts}}|chapter=Godly Sorrow ariſing from the Sufferings of Chriſt|title=Hymns and Spiritual Songs|location=London|publisher=J. Humfreys|page=86|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/bim_eighteenth-century_hymns-and-spiritual-song_watts-isaac_1707/page/86|text=Was it for Crimes that I had done / He groan’d upon the '''Tree'''?}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1997|author=Warren W. Wiersbe|title=The Names of Jesus|passage=When Jesus died on that '''tree''', he bore the awful curse of the law for us so that we might be saved.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2004|author=Jon Courson|title=Jon Courson's Application Commentary|page=1130|passage=Oh, that's not to say Peter's life was easy. In fact, he, too, ended up on a '''tree'''—not hung up by guilt, but crucified upside down on a cross for the sake of the One who not only hung on a '''tree''' for him, but rose and lived within him, empowering him to live a life of incredible impact and ministry.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2015|author=Bruce Thomas|title=God's Purpose for His Creation|passage=Jesus was crucified on a '''tree''' to give us life.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2022|author=Sharmila Panirselvam|title=Life in the Hands of Jesus|passage=Outside of Jerusalem, at Golgotha, Jesus was crucified on a '''tree''' with two other thieves because He claimed to be the king of the Jews.}}\n# {{lb|en|chemistry}} A mass of [[crystal]]s, [[aggregate]]d in [[arborescent]] forms, obtained by [[precipitation]] of a [[metal]] from [[solution]].\n# {{lb|en|cartomancy}} The fifth [[Lenormand]] card.\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|math}} {{alt case|en|TREE}}.\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n{{checksense|en}}\n{{col2|en\n|sapling\n|seedling\n}}\n\n=====Hypernyms=====\n* {{l|en|plant}}\n* {{sense|in graph theory}} {{l|en|graph}}\n\n=====Hyponyms=====\n{{col3|en|title=Of the sense “a perennial plant”\n|cabbage tree\n|chaste tree\n|cherry tree\n|Cherry Tree<qq:places>\n|hip tree\n|Joshua tree\n|lipstick tree\n|pear tree,peartree\n|Pear Tree<qq:place>\n|soap tree|Chinese scholar tree|clique tree|dragon's blood tree|Japanese pagoda tree|kanari tree\n}}\n* See also [[:Category:en:Trees]]\n\n{{col4|en|title=Computing, graph theory, mathematics\n|AVL tree\n|binary tree\n|caterpillar tree\n|DOM tree\n|join tree\n|junction tree\n|Merkle tree\n|red-black tree\n|regression tree\n|search tree\n|spanning tree\n|suffix tree\n|syntax tree\n|XML tree\n}}\n\n{{col4|en|title=Other hyponyms of ''tree''\n|boottree\n|b-tree\n|boron tree|bitterleaf tree|haw tree|Kentucky coffee tree,Kentucky coffee-tree|may tree|prine tree\n|call tree\n|cat tree\n|clothes tree\n|coat tree\n|dead tree\n|decision tree\n|family tree\n|hat tree||feather tree|necklace tree\n|Jesse Tree\n|Kurepa